#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/darken.rst:53
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/darken.rst:57
msgid "Easy Burn"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/darken.rst:61
msgid "This blending mode is called \"Easy Burn\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/darken.rst:63
msgid ""
"Aims to solve issues with Color Burn blending mode by using a formula which "
"falloff is similar to Dodge, but the falloff rate is softer. It is within "
"the range of 0.0f and 1.0f unlike Color Burn mode."
msgstr ""
"焼き込みカラー合成モードの問題を覆い焼きに似た減衰の数式を使うことで、しかし"
"減衰率を緩やかにすることで解決しようとしました。焼き込みカラーモードとは違い"
"0.0fから1.0fの範囲に収まっています。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/darken.rst:68
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/darken/"
"Blending_modes_Easy_Burn_Sample_image_with_dots.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/darken.rst:68
msgid "Left: **Normal**. Right: **Easy Burn**."
msgstr "左: **通常**. 右: **Easy Burn**."

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/darken.rst:70
msgid "Fog Darken"
msgstr "色調"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/darken.rst:74
msgid "Fog Darken (IFS Illusions)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/darken.rst:78
msgid "This blending mode is called \"Fog Darken (IFS Illusions)\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/darken.rst:80
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Darken the image in a way that there is a 'fog' in the end result. This "
#| "is due to the unique property of fog darken in which midtones combined "
#| "are lighter than non-midtones blend."
msgid ""
"Darken the image in a way that there is a 'fog' in the end result. This is "
"due to the unique property of Fog Darken in which midtones combined are "
"lighter than non-midtones blend."
msgstr ""
"結果に'霧'が残るように画像を暗くします。中間色より明るい中間色混合で fog "
"darken とは違うユニークな特性によるものです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/darken.rst:85
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/darken/"
"Blending_modes_Fog_Darken_Sample_image_with_dots.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/darken.rst:85
msgid "Left: **Normal**. Right: **Fog Darken** (exactly the same as Addition)."
msgstr "左: **通常**. 右: **Fog Darken** (加算と全く同じ)."

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/darken.rst:95
msgid "This blending mode is called \"Darken\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/darken.rst:97
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "With the darken, the upper layer's colors are checked for their "
#| "lightness. Only if they are darker than the underlying color on the lower "
#| "layer, will they be visible."
msgid ""
"With Darken, the upper layer's colors are checked for their lightness. Only "
"if they are darker than the underlying color on the lower layer, will they "
"be visible."
msgstr ""
"暗くするでは、上のレイヤー色が照度の確認をされ、下にあるレイヤーの色よりも暗"
"い場合のみ、表示されることになります。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/darken.rst:99
msgid ""
"Is Lighter Gray(0.5, 0.5, 0.5) darker than Darker Gray(0.4, 0.4, 0.4)? = "
"(no, no, no) → Darker Gray(0.4, 0.4, 0.4)"
msgstr ""
"明るいグレー(0.5, 0.5, 0.5) は 暗いグレー(0.4, 0.4, 0.4) よりも暗い？ = (いい"
"え, いいえ, いいえ) → 暗いグレー(0.4, 0.4, 0.4)"

